February 19, 2026
2
3 SENATE BILL NO. 1364 By: Mann
4
5
6 An Act relating to medical marijuana; authorizing the
Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority to develop
7 certain policies and procedures; requiring certain
license applicants to submit certain attestation;
8 requiring disclosure of certain amounts; establishing
certain time frame in which to submit certain
9 attestation; requiring Authority to create and make
publicly available certain form of attestation;
10 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 427.30 of Title 63, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. The Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority is hereby
18 authorized to develop policies and procedures for a medical
19 marijuana business to disclose any outstanding state fees, fines,
20 taxes, or other debts prior to the sale of a medical marijuana
21 business.
22 B. Upon the effective date of this act, current medical
23 marijuana business licensees shall be required to submit under
24 penalty of perjury, an attestation confirming or denying the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1364 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 exis tence of any outstanding state fees, fines, taxes, or other
2 debts and, if applicable, shall disclose the amount of such fees,
3 fines, taxes, or other debts. Medical marijuana business licensees
4 shall, within sixty (60) days after the effective date of this act,
5 submit such attestation to the Authority prior to the sale of a
6 medical marijuana business. The Authority shall prescribe the form
7 of the attestation required under the provisions of this section,
8 and such form shall include an itemized list of any outstanding
9 state fees, fines, taxes, or other debts. The Authority shall make
10 the form available on its publicly accessible Internet website.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS AND INSURANCE
February 19, 2026 - DO PASS
